summary: A tragic plane crash in Wyoming has claimed the lives of three members of the renowned gospel music quartet, The Nelons. The incident has left the gospel music community and fans around the world in mourning. The deceased members, Kristen Nelson, her husband Jason Cramer, and their son Brandon Nelson, were part of the family-run group that has been performing for over four decades. The cause of the crash is under investigation, but the incident has sent shockwaves through the music industry and beyond.

Joining Gretchen was her sister, Alex Walsh, who also qualified for the Olympics. Together, the sisters are known for their impressive swimming skills since childhood. The Walsh sisters received support from their family, who are proud of their achievements. NBC's behind-the-scenes coverage highlighted the sisters' journey to the Olympics. Additionally, Gretchen faced drug testing in 2023 and 2024, which she passed. Despite facing challenges, Gretchen remained focused and achieved her Olympic dream, breaking the existing record in the 100m butterfly.

summary: In a shocking announcement, Michael C. Hall will reprise his iconic role as Dexter Morgan in a new sequel series titled "Dexter: Resurrection." Hall will also provide voiceover narration for the prequel series "Dexter: Original Sin." The "Dexter: Resurrection" series will be set ten years after the events of the original series finale and will follow Dexter as he adjusts to a new life while his dark passenger remains dormant. The "Dexter: Original Sin" prequel series will explore Dexter's early life and the events that shaped him into the serial killer he became. Both series will be available on Showtime and Paramount+.
